 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4" id="how-we-tested">How We Tested</h2>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-300 mb-6">
 <li>Educational value. does it teach real English?</li>
 <li>Child engagement. do kids want to keep using it?</li>
 <li>Safety. no ads, no in-app purchases for kids</li>
 <li>Parent features. progress tracking, time limits</li>
 <li>Value for money. worth the subscription?</li>
 </ul>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4" id="top-5-english-learning-apps-for-kids">Top 5 English Learning Apps for Kids</h2>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">1. Lingokids. Best Overall</h3>
 <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
 <span class="text-yellow-500 text-2xl mr-2">★★★★★</span>
 <span class="font-bold text-xl">8.5/10</span>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Age range:</strong> 2-8 years old</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Price:</strong> Free version available; Lingokids World: $79.88/year (about $6.66/month)</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Lingokids uses games, songs, and videos to teach English. The colorful interface keeps young children engaged. Over 5,000 activities cover vocabulary, listening, reading, and speaking.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What we like:</strong></p>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-300 mb-4">
 <li>Gamified learning with rewards and characters</li>
 <li>No ads in the premium version</li>
 <li>Progress tracking for parents</li>
 <li>Covers all four skills: reading, writing, listening, speaking</li>
 <li>Playlist feature for parents to guide learning</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>What could be better:</strong> Limited value for kids over age 8. Some activities feel more like games than learning.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">2. Duolingo Kids. Best for Structured Learning</h3>
 <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
 <span class="text-yellow-500 text-2xl mr-2">★★★★</span>
 <span class="font-bold text-xl">8.7/10</span>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Age range:</strong> 6-12 years old</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Price:</strong> Included with Duolingo Plus ($12.99/month) or standalone Duolingo Kids $6.99/month</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Duolingo Kids brings the popular Duolingo method to children. Short lessons (2-5 minutes), bright colors, and gamification keep kids motivated. The curriculum follows a clear progression from basics to intermediate skills.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What we like:</strong></p>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-300 mb-4">
 <li>Clear learning progression with levels</li>
 <li>Fun characters and streak rewards</li>
 <li>Covers vocabulary, grammar, and listening</li>
 <li>Easy for children to use independently</li>
 <li>Based on Duolingo's proven methodology</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>What could be better:</strong> Limited speaking practice in the app. Can feel repetitive after a while. Speaking features require kids to read instructions.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">3. Khan Academy Kids. Best Free Option</h3>
 <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
 <span class="text-yellow-500 text-2xl mr-2">★★★★</span>
 <span class="font-bold text-xl">8.3/10</span>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Age range:</strong> 2-8 years old</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Price:</strong> Completely free</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Khan Academy Kids offers thousands of activities covering reading, math, logic, and more. While not exclusively an English learning app, the reading activities are excellent for building literacy skills.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What we like:</strong></p>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-300 mb-4">
 <li>100% free. no subscriptions or ads</li>
 <li>Offline mode available</li>
 <li>Excellent reading and phonics content</li>
 <li>Progress tracking for parents</li>
 <li>Created by education experts</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>What could be better:</strong> Not focused specifically on English as a second language. Less gamified than other options.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">4. ABCmouse. Best for Comprehensive Learning</h3>
 <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
 <span class="text-yellow-500 text-2xl mr-2">★★★★</span>
 <span class="font-bold text-xl">8.4/10</span>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Age range:</strong> 2-8 years old</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Price:</strong> $12.99/month or $79.99/year</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">ABCmouse offers a full learning path with over 10,000 activities. The step-by-step curriculum covers reading, math, science, and art. The "Learning Path" feature guides children through activities in order.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What we like:</strong></p>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-300 mb-4">
 <li>Comprehensive curriculum covering many subjects</li>
 <li>Learning Path keeps children on track</li>
 <li>Huge variety of activities</li>
 <li>Offline mode available</li>
 <li>Excellent for building foundational skills</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>What could be better:</strong> More expensive than alternatives. Can feel overwhelming with too many activities.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">5. Endless Wordplay. Best for Vocabulary</h3>
 <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
 <span class="text-yellow-500 text-2xl mr-2">★★★★</span>
 <span class="font-bold text-xl">8.1/10</span>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Age range:</strong> 3-7 years old</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Price:</strong> $7.99/month or $59.99 one-time purchase</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Endless Wordplay focuses specifically on vocabulary and spelling. The animated monsters make learning word patterns fun. Each level teaches a group of related words (like "-ight" words: light, night, fight).</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>What we like:</strong></p>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-300 mb-4">
 <li>Excellent for vocabulary building</li>
 <li>Fun animations and characters</li>
 <li>Teaches word patterns, not just memorization</li>
 <li>No ads or in-app purchases</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed"><strong>What could be better:</strong> Narrow focus. only vocabulary, not full language skills. Best used alongside another app.</p>

