 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4" id="tips-for-parents">Tips for Parents</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Apps are helpful, but they're not a replacement for real interaction. Here's how to get the most from English learning apps:</p>

 <div class="bg-blue-900/30 border border-blue-700 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
 <h3 class="font-bold mb-4">Do:</h3>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-300">
 <li>Use apps together with your child initially to guide them</li>
 <li>Set time limits (30-45 minutes per day max)</li>
 <li>Check progress reports weekly</li>
 <li>Praise effort, not just completion</li>
 <li>Combine app learning with real English conversation</li>
 </ul>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-red-950/60 border border-red-700 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
 <h3 class="font-bold mb-4">Don't:</h3>
 <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-300">
 <li>Let children use apps unsupervised for long periods</li>
 <li>Use apps as a babysitter. active learning needs parental involvement</li>
 <li>Focus only on screen time. reading books together is equally important</li>
 </ul>
 </div>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4" id="final-verdict">Final Verdict</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">For most families, we recommend starting with <strong>Duolingo Kids</strong> or <strong>Lingokids</strong>. Both are engaging, educational, and worth the subscription cost.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">If budget is a concern, <strong>Khan Academy Kids</strong> is an excellent free option. It's not specifically designed for ESL learners, but the reading content is high quality.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Remember: apps are a tool, not a complete solution. The best results come from combining app learning with real conversations, reading books together, and making English part of your child's daily life.</p>

